docs.lead_paragraph: Dr. Breda, of Natchitoches Parish, La., has devoted much time to experiment with grapes. The result, says the Natchitoches Union, is the complete success of his efforts in producing grapes of the most superior quality, and a demonstration of the fact that wine can be raised profitably, with comparatively little expense.

headline.main: Wisconsin vs. Texas.; MEMORIAL TO THE WISCONSIN LEGISLATURE FOR REDRESS.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Madison (Wis.) State Journal, Feb. 9, says: "The memorial of WILLIAM BLUNT to the Wisconsin Legislature, asking redress for the wrongs and outrages received at the hands of the authorities of Texas, which created quite a flutter on the Democratic side of the Senate when read last Tuesday evening, will be found in to-day's paper.

headline.main: KENTUCKY REPUBLICANISM.; Speech of Hon. Cassius M. Clay, before the Young Men's Republican Club.

docs.lead_paragraph: The announcement that Hon. CASSIUS M. CLAY of Kentucky, would speak at Cooper Institute, last evening, attracted a room full, in spite of the storm. Enough were present to occupy every seat in the large hall, the walls of which were decorated with FREMONT banners and flags.
